<Layout::Group {{waypoint "db"}}>

	<Layout::Text text-l text-f>
		<h3><code>session::db</code></h3>
		<p>The <code>session::db</code> function returns the currently selected database.</p>
		<Code @name="docs-surrealql-functions-session-db.surql" text="API Definition">
			session::db() -> string
		</Code>
		<p>The following example shows this function, and its output, when used in a <Link @link="docs.surrealql.statements.return"><code>RETURN</code></Link> statement:</p>
		<codes vertical>
			<Code @name="docs-surrealql-functions-session-db-input.surql">
				RETURN session::db();
			</Code>
			<Code @name="docs-surrealql-functions-session-db-result.txt">
				"my_db"
			</Code>
		</codes>
	</Layout::Text>

</Layout::Group>

